verses.text:
Hark! the vesper hymn is stealing
O'er the waters soft and clear;
Nearer yet, and nearer pealing,
Soft it breaks upon the ear;
Farther now, now farther stealing,
Soft it fades upon the ear.

Now, like moonbeams faintly gleaming,
On the distant mountain's height;
Now, like distant lamp-light streaming
From some far-off bark at night;
Now, like starlight faintly beaming
In the watches of the night.

Hark! again like waves retreating
To their coral caves below;
Far off, and farther greeting,
Rising now and sinking low;
Now on high, now retreating,
Rising now and sinking low.
